e media, this book unpacks the slippery rhetoric of terror and will prove a vital resource across humanistic and social sciences disciplines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aLanguage and languagesxEtymology. 0aLanguage and languagesxSemantics. 0aPolitical violence. 0aTerror (The English word) 0aTerror (The English word). 0aTerror in literature. 0aTerrorxHistory. 0aTerrorxPhilosophy. 0aTerrorxReligious aspects. 0aTerrorxSocial aspects. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  a9/11.  aconcept history.  ahistory.  anovel.  aphilology.  asubjectivity.  aterror.  aterrorism.  atheory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226600369423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226600369.jpg  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019